document_data.Legacy:
Thayd's goal was to overthrow both Mulhorand and Unther, and take their territories as part of his own Overempire to achieve limitless dominion over the [[Forgotten Realms|Realms]]. In response to his rebellion, Mulhorandi arcane magic was placed under strict control by the [[god-kings]], creating a bureaucracy of priests to keep watch over its developments, thus creating the power structures of Mulhorand that endured well into {{yearlink|1365}}.

The orcs on the other world of his portals discovered these entryways several years later, and used them for the invasions that would later become the [[Orcgate Wars]]. Together, both events orchestrated by the archmage Thayd managed to end the Great Age of the Mulhorandi Empire.{{cite book/Old Empires|3}}

The magocracy of Thay was named after Thayd,{{cite book/The Crimson Gold|48-49|2}}
